"Ugh... not again!" I say, as Hadrik and Arraka both start laughing in the background.

"Barry!" Leila's father shouts into the transceiver again, as Hadrik and Arraka's laughs are intensifying.

"Please wait a moment," Leila's father tells us. "I'm having a bit of trouble reaching one of my companions, due to the thick layer of seredium that-- I'm sorry, is something wrong?"

"Don't mind us!" Hadrik says, as he struggles to stop himself from laughing. "We were just laughing because our friend over here is also named Barry, and this isn't the first time we've met somebody else with his name in the course of our journeys."

